<% @title = "Help" %>

<div class="panel-group" style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; margin-top:10px" id="accordion">
  
  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">
          Add events
        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
      <div class="panel-body">
        
        	<p>Follow these instructions to get started:</p>
  		    <ol>
    			  <li>Sign in to your account, or click to <%= link_to "register", signup_path %>.</li>
    			  <li>Click <strong>Post</strong> to add your event, and add your event details in the form provided.</li>
    			  <li>To edit, delete, or view your events, go to <strong>Account > My events</strong>.</li>
    			  <li>Check the <%= link_to "calendar", calendar_path %> to see all events!</li>
  		    </ol>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">
          Sync with gcal
        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <div style="overflow:auto;">
        <p>To sync with google calendar:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Sign in to your google account to access your calendar.</li>
			<li>Click the down-arrow next to <strong>Other calendars</strong> (located on the left panel).</li>
			<li>Select <strong>Add by URL</strong> from the menu.</li>
			<li>Enter the following address in the field provided: https://hmsevents.herokuapp.com/export.ics</li>
			<li>Click <strong>Add calendar</strong>. The calendar will appear in the <strong>Other calendars</strong> section of the calendar list to the left.</li>
		</ol>
    <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">There is no way to manually set the refresh rate in gcal, so use iCal or another calendar service if possible.</div>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">
          Sync with iCal
        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <div style="overflow:auto;">
        <p>To sync with iCal:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Open the <strong>Calendar</strong> program (in Applications). </li>
			<li>From the <strong>File</strong> menu, select <strong>New Calendar Subscription</strong>.</li>
			<li>Enter the following address in the field provided: https://hmsevents.herokuapp.com/export.ics</li>
			<li>Update the Auto-refresh frequency to <strong>Every day</strong> (just in case an event has been recently added or updated), then click OK.</li>
			<li>The events should now appear in your calendar.</li>
		</ol>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-info">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">
          Contact us
        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        If you need any help, or have any suggestions or concerns, please email us at <strong>hms.eventscal@gmail.com</strong> - we'll get back to you as soon as possible.
        <br><br>
        Thanks!
        <br>
        Sachin, Abhayjit, and Diana
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>



